		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=darkparable&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hi all,<br><br>I just made a new DE SK about a week ago and I had a few questions for everyone. <br><br>A little background: I am nearly level 8 and have had some pretty good fortune (for evil people the other high level de's are pretty nice to us newer characters). I was killing spiderlings non-stop and collecting silks hoping that some tailor or smith would need some and I could get money to replace my training tunic and rusty weapons. I saw a 50th level wizard killing spiderlings so I did the &quot;WTS s silk routine...&quot; She was collecting silks for her friend a smith. I met the smith sold him the silks. He said that if I would collect silks for him he would make me a suit of banded--seemed eminently fair. I gave him two more stacks. He gave me a complete suit of banded and his wizard friend gave me a darkedged two hander--NICE SWORD. On my own initiative I've given him about 4-5 more stacks of s silks and pelts for leather padding...he was pretty surpised and said he'll make me some fine steel items and plate--I wasn't seeking anything else but that would be very cool. I also was given by other people a runic carver, a velium two handed sword, and a bronze long sword. I have about 100pp in the bank from earlier pelt and bone chip sales.<br><br>Now to the questions:<br><br>Since my armor needs seem pretty handled for right now what should I purchase or save for to purchase next. All weapon skills are maxed except for 2hb and piercing. I was thinking a good one handed weapon (mainly for training purposes with a shield) or strength items (I have a base 90 str thats where I pumped my points).<br><br>I'm thinking on passing the carver off to another new shadowknight. But I was thinking on selling the other two weapons for the aforementioned items. What do you guys think?<br><br>Also how long should I stay in Nek forest before moving to other areas?<br><br>Finally, how worried do I have to be moving to other areas with the KOS thing? Any advice anyone could give on faction (and not screwing up my home town faction would be appreciated).<br><br>Thanks,<br><br>Adrioch<br>7th lvl SK<br>Morell-Thule</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >5 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
