		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=259987"><span id=Scholar>jonnypanic</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>61 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.39]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=jonnypanic&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I rather agree with xaanru, here, prices on spiderling silks are about the same on Saryrn server, if you don't want to go sit in baz and sell them, at least aim for a field price of 5-10 plat or so per silk. This smith is taking you for a ride, altho I guess at least your getting something better than what you started with. Take it as a lesson learned, and go make some real cash.<br><br>Velium Fire rings are pretty easy to find, and would be an EXCELLENT idea... each ring is 6 AC and 65 hps. They cost about... 320 plat, I think... to make and the parts can be storebought: a fire opal from any jeweler and a bar of velium (BAR of velium, not piece or block) from the jeweler in Thurgadin. Should be pretty easy to find someone who will try to make em for you for a small donation, altho they never trivial so there's always a chance of failure... group with whoever's doing the combine to see if they really do it, you'll see the success or failure messages that way. You can usually save a few plat this way, coz anyone who makes em for bazaar selling will want a noticeable profit. <br><br>Other gear of note would be Black Sapphire Electrum earrings (with I think 25 hps and mana), a shield as discussed in another thread in this forum (or at least a Clay Guardian shield), and perhaps a Shard of Night (if you can kill for silks enough to save up for it), or at least a fun lil weapon like a Crystalline Spider Fang (10 dmg, 22 delay, and procs a 12 dmg spell sometimes when you attack). Other than that, as xaanru said, just sell your silks, shop around the Bazaar, and find whatever gear you can afford. Aim for higher AC, hps, stamina, and str. Work on Int and mana as you see fit, since you're about to get your first spells and prolly want to play with em a bit... they're nothing special to start, but keep in mind it gets better as you progress =)<br><br><i><span class=sm>Edited, Wed Sep&nbsp;&nbsp;8 04:36:52 2004 by jonnypanic</span class=sm></i></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>*****************<br>Ten days without sleep lurches and bubbles toward him and through him and away</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
